fi.vtt.nubomedia.kurentoroomclientandroid

Class KurentoRoomAPI

  • java.lang.Object
    • fi.vtt.nubomedia.kurentoroomclientandroid.KurentoAPI
      • fi.vtt.nubomedia.kurentoroomclientandroid.KurentoRoomAPI

  • public class KurentoRoomAPI
extends KurentoAPI
    Class that handles all Room API calls and passes asynchronous responses and notifications to a RoomListener interface.

    • Constructor Detail

      • KurentoRoomAPI

        public KurentoRoomAPI(LooperExecutor executor,
                      java.lang.String uri,
                      RoomListener listener)
        Constructor that initializes required instances and parameters for the API calls. WebSocket connections are not established in the constructor. User is responsible for opening, closing and checking if the connection is open through the corresponding API calls.
        Parameters:
        executor - is the asynchronous UI-safe executor for tasks.
        uri - is the web socket link to the room web services.
        listener - interface handles the callbacks for responses, notifications and errors.

    • Method Detail

      • sendJoinRoom

        public void sendJoinRoom(java.lang.String userId,
                         java.lang.String roomId,
                         int id)
        Method for the user to join the room. If the room does not exist previously, it will be created. The response will contain the list of users and their streams in the room.
        Parameters:
        userId - is the username as it appears to all other users.
        roomId - is the name of the room to be joined.
        id - is an index number to track the corresponding response message to this request.

      • sendLeaveRoom

        public void sendLeaveRoom(int id)
        Method will leave the current room.
        Parameters:
        id - is an index number to track the corresponding response message to this request.

      • sendPublishVideo

        public void sendPublishVideo(java.lang.String sdpOffer,
                             boolean doLoopback,
                             int id)
        Method to publish a video. The response will contain the sdpAnswer attribute.
        Parameters:
        sdpOffer - is a string sent by the client
        doLoopback - is a boolean value enabling media loopback
        id - is an index number to track the corresponding response message to this request.

      • sendUnpublishVideo

        public void sendUnpublishVideo(int id)
        Method unpublishes a previously published video.
        Parameters:
        id - is an index number to track the corresponding response message to this request.

      • sendReceiveVideoFrom

        public void sendReceiveVideoFrom(java.lang.String sender,
                                 java.lang.String sdpOffer,
                                 int id)
        Method represents the client's request to receive media from participants in the room that published their media. The response will contain the sdpAnswer attribute.
        Parameters:
        sender - is a combination of publisher's name and his currently opened stream (usually webcam) separated by underscore. For example: userid_webcam
        sdpOffer - is the SDP offer sent by this client.
        id - is an index number to track the corresponding response message to this request.

      • sendUnsubscribeFromVideo

        public void sendUnsubscribeFromVideo(java.lang.String userId,
                                     java.lang.String streamId,
                                     int id)
        Method represents a client's request to stop receiving media from a given publisher. Response will contain the sdpAnswer attribute.
        Parameters:
        userId - is the publisher's username.
        streamId - is the name of the stream (typically webcam)
        id - is an index number to track the corresponding response message to this request.

      • sendOnIceCandidate

        public void sendOnIceCandidate(java.lang.String endpointName,
                               java.lang.String candidate,
                               java.lang.String sdpMid,
                               java.lang.String sdpMLineIndex)
        Method carries the information about the ICE candidate gathered on the client side. This information is required to implement the trickle ICE mechanism.
        Parameters:
        endpointName - is the username of the peer whose ICE candidate was found
        candidate - contains the candidate attribute information
        sdpMid - is the media stream identification, "audio" or "video", for the m-line, this candidate is associated with.
        sdpMLineIndex - is the index (starting at 0) of the m-line in the SDP, this candidate is associated with.

      • sendMessage

        public void sendMessage(java.lang.String roomId,
                        java.lang.String userId,
                        java.lang.String message,
                        int id)
        Method sends a message from the user to all other participants in the room.
        Parameters:
        roomId - is the name of the room.
        userId - is the username of the user sending the message.
        message - is the text message sent to the room.
        id - is an index number to track the corresponding response message to this request.

      • sendCustomRequest

        public void sendCustomRequest(java.lang.String[] names,
                              java.lang.String[] values,
                              int id)
        Method to send any custom requests that are not directly implemented by the Room server.
        Parameters:
        names - is an array of parameter names.
        values - is an array of parameter values where the index is corresponding with the applicable name value in the names array.
        id - is an index number to track the corresponding response message to this request.
